WEBVTT

00:04.178 --> 00:04.352
.

00:04.395 --> 00:07.007
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:07.050 --> 00:09.748
sexually-based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:09.792 --> 00:12.273
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:12.316 --> 00:14.057
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:14.101 --> 00:15.493
are members of an elite squad

00:15.537 --> 00:17.669
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.713 --> 00:19.584
These are their stories.

00:21.108 --> 00:23.458
[pop music]

00:23.501 --> 00:25.634
- It's going to be amazing.

00:25.677 --> 00:27.462
- My daddy says
you're a hard worker.

00:27.505 --> 00:28.550
- [laughs]
- He does?

00:28.593 --> 00:30.682
Well, that's good to know.
[laughs]

00:30.726 --> 00:33.120
- It's true.
- Do you have a gun too?

00:33.163 --> 00:36.427
- I do, but I don't
bring it to parties.

00:38.951 --> 00:41.302
Wow, your family's so lovely.

00:41.345 --> 00:43.913
And you didn't tell me
that your wife is gorgeous.

00:43.956 --> 00:45.523
And--and hilarious.

00:45.567 --> 00:48.352
- Lamai balances me out.
All right.

00:48.396 --> 00:50.963
Heads-up,
I know that look in her eye.

00:51.007 --> 00:54.054
- Olivia, did Chris tell you--
- You know I didn't.

00:54.097 --> 00:56.186
- Our dear friend, Edgar.

00:56.230 --> 01:00.582
He's a partner at my old firm.
Edgar, Olivia.

01:00.625 --> 01:03.063
- Hello.
- Olivia.

01:03.106 --> 01:05.935
You're as stunning
as Lamai said you were.

01:05.978 --> 01:08.677
- [laughs]

01:11.245 --> 01:12.724
- Hey.
- Oh.

01:12.768 --> 01:14.161
- You okay?

01:14.204 --> 01:16.641
- Yeah, well, I spent
the weekend with my mother.

01:16.685 --> 01:19.296
- Beth okay?
So that's a no.

01:19.340 --> 01:21.429
Other than that?
- What, end of the shift,

01:21.472 --> 01:23.170
I'm sent to Special Frauds

01:23.213 --> 01:26.782
where a sticky-fingered church
bookkeeper may want to flip.

01:26.825 --> 01:29.219
Does life get better than that?
- So that's another no?

01:29.263 --> 01:32.135
Right over here.

01:32.179 --> 01:35.573
Ms. Blake, this is Detective
Rollins from Special Victims.

01:35.617 --> 01:38.402
I've told her a spot audit
revealed that you've embezzled

01:38.446 --> 01:40.404
more than $400,000
from your church.

01:40.448 --> 01:41.579
- And you're looking
to trade information

01:41.623 --> 01:44.800
about a sexual predator?
Who?

01:44.843 --> 01:46.497
- It's okay.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.108
- He's an official
at my church.

01:48.151 --> 01:50.980
- Go on.

01:51.023 --> 01:54.810
- Cards on the table, Sherry.

01:54.853 --> 01:56.290
- He's had sexual relations

01:56.333 --> 01:58.422
with teenage girls
in the congregation

01:58.466 --> 02:00.772
and used church funds
to pay them off.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.252
[tense music]

02:02.296 --> 02:03.993
- Gonna need his name.
- We're gonna need assurances.

02:04.036 --> 02:05.429
- As I've told you,
the DA will consider any--

02:05.473 --> 02:07.475
- I'm worried about the NYPD.

02:07.518 --> 02:09.781
- Excuse me?
- This church official?

02:09.825 --> 02:12.871
He's a close personal friend
of your boss.

02:12.915 --> 02:15.744
♪

02:15.787 --> 02:19.487
- So, normally I stumble
my way through grace.

02:19.530 --> 02:23.621
- No, no.
[laughter]

02:23.665 --> 02:26.276
- Uh, but Reverend Chase,
would you do us the honors?

02:26.320 --> 02:30.062
- Shall we?

02:30.106 --> 02:31.673
Dear Lord, thank you
for the gift

02:31.716 --> 02:33.892
of gathering in the warmth
of the Garland home

02:33.936 --> 02:35.546
on a cold winter's night,

02:35.590 --> 02:38.462
to visit with old friends
and to meet new ones,

02:38.506 --> 02:41.291
to savor
Lamai's masterful cooking...

02:41.335 --> 02:43.337
To--
[doorbell rings]

02:43.380 --> 02:45.469
To be interrupted
by a doorbell.

02:45.513 --> 02:47.993
[laughter]
- Excuse me.

02:48.037 --> 02:49.952
- Cheers, everyone.

02:49.995 --> 02:52.128
all: Cheers.
- Here's to a lovely evening.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.651
♪

02:53.695 --> 02:55.697
- Sorry to bother you, Chief.
- We tried calling.

02:55.740 --> 02:58.047
- It's a no-cell phones dinner.
Your captain's here.

02:58.090 --> 03:00.310
- We know.
We need a minute.

03:00.354 --> 03:04.140
- Come in.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.969
- Carisi, Rollins,
what's going on?

03:07.012 --> 03:09.450
- We got a credible tip about
a serial sexual predator.

03:09.493 --> 03:10.842
- Couldn't wait until morning?

03:10.886 --> 03:12.496
- The informant claims
it's someone you know.

03:12.540 --> 03:13.889
She wants assurances that

03:13.932 --> 03:15.673
you'll let
the investigation proceed.

03:15.717 --> 03:17.501
- Of course I will.
Who is it?

03:17.545 --> 03:20.765
- Reverend Delman Chase.

03:20.809 --> 03:22.202
- I find that
very hard to believe.

03:22.245 --> 03:24.726
- Wasn't that just him
saying grace?

03:24.769 --> 03:26.684
♪

03:26.728 --> 03:28.251
How well do you
know each other?

03:28.295 --> 03:31.211
- H-he and his wife Laura
are like family.

03:31.254 --> 03:35.345
Been my spiritual advisor
for over a decade.

03:35.389 --> 03:37.042
He was the minister
at my wedding.

03:37.086 --> 03:43.962
♪

03:49.359 --> 03:52.319
[dramatic music]

03:52.362 --> 03:59.500
♪

04:36.232 --> 04:37.538
- So Garland's minister's

04:37.581 --> 04:39.061
doing teenage girls
at his church?

04:39.104 --> 04:40.628
- Fin, we don't know that.

04:40.671 --> 04:41.933
- Then why would
this accountant make it up?

04:41.977 --> 04:43.979
- Because she's facing
serious fraud charges.

04:44.022 --> 04:45.807
Anyway, Garland
doesn't believe it.

04:45.850 --> 04:48.853
- So he's gonna shut us down?
- No, that's not his way.

04:48.897 --> 04:50.290
Or his call.

04:50.333 --> 04:52.770
- Hey, check this out.
- Hey.

04:52.814 --> 04:55.860
[Christian praise song
playing]

04:55.904 --> 05:02.824
♪

05:04.434 --> 05:07.002
- Praise dancing
at Harlem Heights Baptist?

05:07.045 --> 05:08.612
- Turns out Reverend Chase

05:08.656 --> 05:11.441
is a big supporter of the
church's all-girl dance troupe.

05:11.485 --> 05:12.616
They perform
all over the country,

05:12.660 --> 05:13.965
win all kinds of awards.

05:14.009 --> 05:15.358
- Whoo!
[cheers and applause]

05:15.402 --> 05:17.882
Hallelujah!
Oh, praise the Lord.

05:17.926 --> 05:19.057
[laughs]

05:19.101 --> 05:22.017
Oh, yeah, wonderful job.

05:22.060 --> 05:24.672
Oh, that was wonderful.

05:26.413 --> 05:27.805
- Good job, good job.
- Whoo!

05:27.849 --> 05:30.460
Our praise dancers
always lift my spirit.

05:30.504 --> 05:31.983
- Amen.
- Amen.

05:32.027 --> 05:34.421
- We're so blessed.
- We are so blessed.

05:34.464 --> 05:37.075
- That's Chase's wife
and co-pastor, Laura.

05:37.119 --> 05:39.339
They've been at Harlem Heights
for 20 years.

05:39.382 --> 05:41.384
Uh, their sermons
are nationally broadcast.

05:41.428 --> 05:43.778
- So he's a for-profit pastor?
- Uh, yeah.

05:43.821 --> 05:46.389
They got the two mansions,
a church-leased private plane.

05:46.433 --> 05:49.392
But he also runs a charity that
works with local non-profits.

05:49.436 --> 05:50.611
- And he started
a charter school

05:50.654 --> 05:52.047
for underprivileged girls.

05:52.090 --> 05:54.789
And the church also funds
a dorm for at-risk youth.

05:54.832 --> 05:57.269
- Okay, that could be
a hunting ground.

05:57.313 --> 05:58.619
What do we have on his payouts?

05:58.662 --> 06:02.013
- Uh, Chase told his bookkeeper
that these checks

06:02.057 --> 06:05.060
were for families in need,
the girls' college funds.

06:05.103 --> 06:06.670
- Code for hush money.

06:06.714 --> 06:08.368
- Over 50 checks
from the last seven years,

06:08.411 --> 06:11.327
all varying amounts,
almost all 15K or under.

06:11.371 --> 06:15.331
- Uh, sorry to interrupt.
Captain.

06:15.375 --> 06:19.509
- Yes, okay, great.
Here you go.

06:20.205 --> 06:21.555
Come in.

06:21.598 --> 06:23.034
- Thank you for
coming last night.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.080
- It was a lovely evening.

06:25.123 --> 06:27.517
- Huh, until it wasn't.

06:27.561 --> 06:32.696
Look, after everyone left,
it, uh...

06:32.740 --> 06:34.437
it crossed my mind
to call Del back.

06:34.481 --> 06:35.917
- You wanted to give him
a heads-up?

06:35.960 --> 06:38.354
- I did, because I don't
believe he's capable of this.

06:38.398 --> 06:42.140
But Lamai had the good legal
sense to talk me out of that.

06:42.184 --> 06:44.229
To be clear, you're in control
of the investigation.

06:44.273 --> 06:46.275
I'll recuse.

06:46.318 --> 06:48.016
You can report
to the Chief of D's.

06:48.059 --> 06:50.279
- I appreciate that.

06:50.322 --> 06:53.543
But because he trusts you...

06:53.587 --> 06:56.372
and the community trusts you...

06:56.416 --> 06:58.592
I may need your help
with this.

07:00.463 --> 07:02.247
- Okay.

07:02.291 --> 07:05.033
In that case, Laura Chase
pulled me aside last night.

07:05.076 --> 07:07.427
She's worried about
the embezzlement.

07:07.470 --> 07:09.777
Might be an opening.

07:12.954 --> 07:15.217
- We appreciate your
cooperation, Reverend Chase.

07:15.260 --> 07:17.393
- Call me Laura.
But aren't you Special Victims?

07:17.437 --> 07:20.701
- We are, but Chris Garland
asked us to look into this

07:20.744 --> 07:23.834
on behalf of Special Frauds.
- Christian's a good man.

07:23.878 --> 07:26.054
When I heard Sherry Blake
stole collection-plate money

07:26.097 --> 07:27.795
to go on shopping sprees,
I was sickened.

07:27.838 --> 07:30.101
- Not just collections.
We flagged some checks that

07:30.145 --> 07:32.756
may or may not be legitimate.
W-would you mind taking a look?

07:32.800 --> 07:35.411
- Of course.
Let's go to my office.

07:35.455 --> 07:39.023
These two--we never used
a catering service, I'm sure.

07:39.067 --> 07:40.808
- Okay, so put those
in the fraudulent pile.

07:40.851 --> 07:44.072
And now we have
three different car payments.

07:44.115 --> 07:46.727
- Yeah, we each have our own
car and there's a church van.

07:46.770 --> 07:49.730
- We also found a, uh, series
of checks made out to--

07:49.773 --> 07:52.384
to different girls.
Do you recognize this name?

07:52.428 --> 07:54.125
- Yeah, Breyona Taylor--
she's a student.

07:54.169 --> 07:56.040
$10,000.

07:56.084 --> 07:58.913
The church sometimes helps
young girls with family need.

07:58.956 --> 08:00.654
- Yeah.

08:00.697 --> 08:03.395
This one is from
four years ago.

08:03.439 --> 08:07.269
- Destiny Hall?
We had such high hopes for her.

08:07.312 --> 08:09.358
Poor girl just lost her way.

08:09.401 --> 08:11.839
[tense music]

08:11.882 --> 08:13.449
$75,000?

08:13.493 --> 08:15.320
- Yeah, three checks
in the same month.

08:15.364 --> 08:16.800
Renee Lee, 75,000.

08:16.844 --> 08:19.629
Sade Ferguson, 75,000.

08:19.673 --> 08:22.327
And $100,000
PraiseRaise fund

08:22.371 --> 08:24.808
for, uh, Sade Lee.

08:24.852 --> 08:26.549
- [sighs]
Renee is a student,

08:26.593 --> 08:29.117
and Sade is her mom.
And they were struggling.

08:29.160 --> 08:32.512
But there's no way the church
would've paid out $1/4 million.

08:32.555 --> 08:33.991
[tense music]

08:34.035 --> 08:36.037
[exhales slowly]
Sister Sherry must have

08:36.080 --> 08:38.605
written out the checks
and laundered them.

08:38.648 --> 08:41.172
My husband will be
beside himself.

08:41.216 --> 08:43.218
♪

08:43.261 --> 08:44.654
- Yes, it's my check.

08:44.698 --> 08:45.829
It's made out to me,
Breyona Taylor.

08:45.873 --> 08:47.439
- Can you tell us
what it was for?

08:47.483 --> 08:49.529
- I told the Rev that I wanted
to go to medical school

08:49.572 --> 08:51.008
to become a pediatrician.

08:51.052 --> 08:53.533
He said it would cost a lot,
but he could help.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.099
- And he just gave you
the check?

08:55.143 --> 08:58.538
- We put it in an account,
just like that.

08:58.581 --> 09:00.409
- Did he expect anything
in return?

09:00.452 --> 09:01.758
♪

09:01.802 --> 09:03.804
- Just to keep
working towards my dream

09:03.847 --> 09:05.936
and to give all glory to God.

09:05.980 --> 09:08.243
- The Reverend called it
a down payment on my future.

09:08.286 --> 09:11.202
- What that mean?

09:11.246 --> 09:13.596
- It meant keep my mouth shut.
- About what?

09:13.640 --> 09:15.380
- About him being nasty.

09:15.424 --> 09:16.686
He gave me a loan,

09:16.730 --> 09:18.558
asked if I have bad thoughts,

09:18.601 --> 09:20.995
asked me to tell him
about my temptations.

09:21.038 --> 09:23.606
- Anything else happen?
- I shut him down.

09:23.650 --> 09:26.609
Took his check.
That money is long gone.

09:26.653 --> 09:29.264
- You ever tell anyone?
- [scoffs]

09:29.307 --> 09:31.788
Everyone at that church
thinks he's God.

09:31.832 --> 09:38.012
♪

09:38.055 --> 09:39.883
- Thanks for speaking
with us, Michelle.

09:39.927 --> 09:40.841
- You're here about
that accountant?

09:40.884 --> 09:41.885
- Everyone knows about it?

09:41.929 --> 09:44.018
- Yeah.
The girls are all upset.

09:44.061 --> 09:45.672
I'm the dorm mom,
so I hear it all.

09:45.715 --> 09:47.717
- Is Renee Lee here today?

09:47.761 --> 09:51.112
- Front and center,
like always.

09:51.155 --> 09:52.853
- Thanks.

09:52.896 --> 09:55.116
- Reverend Chase is
generous to all us girls.

09:55.159 --> 09:58.032
He's a true Christian.
- I'm sure he is, but...

09:58.075 --> 10:00.251
$250,000?

10:00.295 --> 10:03.559
- My mom broke her back.
She hasn't worked in a year.

10:03.603 --> 10:04.908
- And was that
the only reason

10:04.952 --> 10:06.083
the Reverend gave
your family the money?

10:06.127 --> 10:08.129
- Like, breaking
your back isn't enough?

10:08.172 --> 10:10.566
- It's just a lot more
than the other donations

10:10.610 --> 10:12.524
made by the church,

10:12.568 --> 10:15.179
and if the Reverend
asked for anything in return--

10:15.223 --> 10:18.008
- Like what?
You saying the Rev's a creeper?

10:18.052 --> 10:20.358
He's not.

10:20.402 --> 10:22.839
Anyway, I gotta rehearse now.

10:24.754 --> 10:26.974
- I'm new and all, but--
- You're not that new.

10:27.017 --> 10:29.890
Something happened here,
and it wasn't spiritual.

10:29.933 --> 10:32.675
- Who's gonna
tell Chief Garland?

10:34.938 --> 10:36.592
- How long's it been
since we've done this?

10:36.636 --> 10:38.899
- Too long.

10:38.942 --> 10:40.640
And I thought here would be
a better place to talk

10:40.683 --> 10:41.945
than either of our offices.

10:41.989 --> 10:43.294
- If this is about
the embezzlement, Del,

10:43.338 --> 10:45.035
I assure you the investigation
will proceed

10:45.079 --> 10:46.863
with due diligence.
- Will it?

10:46.907 --> 10:49.170
There are bitter and racist
eyes on us, Christian.

10:49.213 --> 10:51.520
Eyes that don't wanna see me
raise up this community

10:51.563 --> 10:53.174
through my church, my school.

10:53.217 --> 10:57.265
Eyes that don't wanna see
a black man rise in the NYPD.

10:57.308 --> 10:59.310
- But I have risen.

11:00.529 --> 11:02.096
As have you.

11:02.139 --> 11:04.707
- These investigators are
making salacious implications,

11:04.751 --> 11:06.578
concocting conspiracies.

11:06.622 --> 11:08.015
I worry folks will think

11:08.058 --> 11:09.973
there must be fire
underneath that smoke.

11:10.017 --> 11:12.280
Whatever stories
your people are hearing,

11:12.323 --> 11:14.369
I need to know.

11:14.412 --> 11:16.458
Promise me you won't be
a corbie-messenger.

11:16.501 --> 11:19.461
- [chuckles]
Understood.

11:19.504 --> 11:22.116
- That's all I need to know.

11:22.159 --> 11:25.380
I'm always here
for you, Christian.

11:27.556 --> 11:31.429
At this point, I'll resign.

11:31.473 --> 11:33.736
If I taught you anything,

11:33.780 --> 11:36.565
it's how to protect your king.

11:36.608 --> 11:38.698
[suspenseful music]

11:38.741 --> 11:40.308
- All right, man.

11:40.351 --> 11:47.271
♪

11:51.580 --> 11:53.887
- Well?

11:53.930 --> 11:56.890
- Protested far too much.
- [sighs]

11:56.933 --> 11:59.544
- He asked for my word
that I have his back.

11:59.588 --> 12:01.111
♪

12:01.155 --> 12:04.158
- I'm so sorry.
- So am I.

12:04.811 --> 12:06.769
I have a sick feeling
the Lord had nothing to do

12:06.813 --> 12:08.597
with why he wrote those checks.

12:08.640 --> 12:12.296
♪

12:16.039 --> 12:16.431
.

12:16.474 --> 12:18.259
- I'm happy to help
if I can, Captain.

12:18.302 --> 12:20.304
My wife said this was about

12:20.348 --> 12:21.784
the checks
to Renee Lee's mother.

12:21.828 --> 12:23.438
- Yeah, your wife thought

12:23.481 --> 12:25.745
that they were fraudulent.

12:29.357 --> 12:31.489
- No, the other ones
she caught were,

12:31.533 --> 12:34.057
but on these,
Laura was mistaken.

12:34.101 --> 12:35.624
- So the quarter million
is legit?

12:35.667 --> 12:37.060
- I don't recall
the exact amount,

12:37.104 --> 12:38.409
but Renee's needs were great.

12:38.453 --> 12:41.064
- How do you mean?

12:41.108 --> 12:42.805
- Renee's mother,
who had worked on her feet

12:42.849 --> 12:45.895
her entire life,
suffered a serious back injury.

12:45.939 --> 12:48.245
She couldn't pay
her mortgage, her heat.

12:48.289 --> 12:51.814
Renee would've had to drop out
of school, go home, work.

12:51.858 --> 12:54.208
And her home was
a troubled environment.

12:54.251 --> 12:56.384
- So you saved her?

12:56.427 --> 12:59.126
- The church saved her
with the Lord's help.

12:59.169 --> 13:00.780
- Okay.

13:00.823 --> 13:03.783
Did the church's hierarchy
approve these checks?

13:03.826 --> 13:05.393
- Payments are
at my discretion,

13:05.436 --> 13:07.047
with the Lord's guidance.

13:07.090 --> 13:09.614
- So the Lord told you to
make three separate payments,

13:09.658 --> 13:12.182
including a check
made out directly to Renee?

13:12.226 --> 13:14.097
- Separating the payments

13:14.141 --> 13:16.839
was definitely
Sister Sherry's idea.

13:16.883 --> 13:19.799
And--and I don't recall
this last one at all.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.975
I'd say ask her,

13:22.018 --> 13:24.847
but we already know we
can't believe a word she says.

13:24.891 --> 13:29.199
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a sermon to prepare.

13:29.243 --> 13:32.028
- About yielding to temptation?

13:32.072 --> 13:36.250
- No, about forgiveness.

13:36.293 --> 13:39.253
[dramatic music]

13:39.296 --> 13:43.039
♪

13:43.083 --> 13:46.216
- So where are we?
- Giving money away is legal.

13:46.260 --> 13:49.872
Chase claims not to recall
one payment to Renee.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.613
Renee insists

13:51.656 --> 13:54.268
that the Reverend
gave her and her mother

13:54.311 --> 13:57.271
all three checks,
no strings attached.

13:57.314 --> 13:59.534
- So what does the mother say?
- She lives up in Syracuse.

13:59.577 --> 14:02.450
I sent Fin and Kat up there.
- Good.

14:02.493 --> 14:03.973
Tell them they can
threaten her with fraud

14:04.017 --> 14:06.323
if she doesn't tell the truth.
I'm not in a forgiving mood.

14:09.152 --> 14:10.545
- Fraud at the church?

14:10.588 --> 14:12.373
Well, that's terrible.

14:12.416 --> 14:14.505
Well, my money's legitimate.
I hurt myself.

14:14.549 --> 14:16.681
- Yeah, we heard that
you had some kind of a fall.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.596
- I had a table full
of Karens riding me,

14:18.640 --> 14:21.164
and cleared too fast
and I slipped.

14:21.208 --> 14:22.557
You know, I would
have lost my home

14:22.600 --> 14:25.212
if Reverend Chase
hadn't sent that check.

14:25.255 --> 14:26.822
- And the PraiseRaise fund?

14:26.866 --> 14:28.345
- Well, that was
for my medical.

14:28.389 --> 14:30.304
Renee kept saying,
"Just keep praying

14:30.347 --> 14:31.740
and trusting in God, and--"

14:31.783 --> 14:33.916
- But all the money came
from the Reverend's church.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.700
- The Reverend
always looked out for her.

14:35.744 --> 14:37.789
She was a wild child,

14:37.833 --> 14:39.400
and I was about
to put her out the house.

14:39.443 --> 14:41.097
But then my sister
saw the Reverend on TV,

14:41.141 --> 14:44.927
so Renee sends in
her praise dance audition tape,

14:44.971 --> 14:47.277
and right away he sends
a ticket for her

14:47.321 --> 14:50.193
to come to New York.
It was a miracle.

14:50.237 --> 14:52.804
- Praise Jesus.
- Amen.

14:52.848 --> 14:54.676
- Have you ever
met the Reverend?

14:54.719 --> 14:56.678
- No.
Only person I've ever spoken

14:56.721 --> 14:59.855
with is the dorm mom girl,
Michelle.

14:59.899 --> 15:03.032
She told me how much
everyone loves Renee.

15:04.251 --> 15:06.427
- $250,000?
Are you sure?

15:06.470 --> 15:08.037
- It seems like
a lot to you.

15:08.081 --> 15:10.431
- After all he's done for her,
and this is how she repays him?

15:10.474 --> 15:11.867
- What do you mean, Michelle?

15:11.911 --> 15:13.521
- Reverend Chase would never
give her all that money.

15:13.564 --> 15:15.697
Renee must have stolen it.

15:15.740 --> 15:18.482
Maybe she's in on it
with that bookkeeper.

15:18.526 --> 15:19.701
He's such a good man.

15:19.744 --> 15:21.485
He doesn't see people
for who they are.

15:21.529 --> 15:23.923
- That's what we thought.

15:23.966 --> 15:26.490
Thank you.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.363
- There's no way
Renee stole that money.

15:29.406 --> 15:30.712
- No, but maybe
we should give her

15:30.755 --> 15:32.018
a chance to refute the charge.

15:32.061 --> 15:33.933
- You want to use
a false charge as leverage

15:33.976 --> 15:35.499
to pressure a victim
to disclose?

15:35.543 --> 15:37.371
- He's a revered minister.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.155
If we want to make this case,

15:39.199 --> 15:41.810
we may not have a choice.

15:41.853 --> 15:43.029
- I hate to say this, Renee,

15:43.072 --> 15:45.292
but you could be in
serious trouble here.

15:45.335 --> 15:46.771
- Why am I in trouble?

15:46.815 --> 15:48.034
- Well, the Reverend doesn't
remember the check

15:48.077 --> 15:50.384
made out to you.
- That's impossible.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.647
He handed it to me.
- He did?

15:52.690 --> 15:57.043
What was it for?
- Like I said, expenses.

15:57.086 --> 15:58.914
My future.
- Huh.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.698
Well, you and your mom
got over ten times more

16:00.742 --> 16:02.570
than anybody else.

16:02.613 --> 16:05.225
Now, it's been suggested
that, uh, that you stole it.

16:05.268 --> 16:06.922
- I didn't steal anything.

16:06.966 --> 16:08.054
- I hope not.

16:08.097 --> 16:10.360
Charges for grand larceny
are serious.

16:10.404 --> 16:12.710
- I could go to jail?

16:12.754 --> 16:15.626
[soft dramatic music]

16:15.670 --> 16:16.801
♪

16:16.845 --> 16:18.412
I just did what he wanted.

16:18.455 --> 16:20.414
- And what--
what was that, honey?

16:20.457 --> 16:22.242
♪

16:22.285 --> 16:25.288
- If I tell the truth,
can my mom keep the money?

16:25.332 --> 16:26.942
I wasn't lying about her.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.509
- We're gonna do
everything we can to help you.

16:28.552 --> 16:31.642
- But you need to tell us
the whole story.

16:33.122 --> 16:36.212
- When I started at the school,
my grades were bad,

16:36.256 --> 16:39.259
really bad.

16:39.302 --> 16:42.784
He called me into his office,
but he didn't yell at me.

16:42.827 --> 16:46.831
He said he would
tutor me privately.

16:46.875 --> 16:49.617
It would be our secret.

16:49.660 --> 16:53.055
- Did you and he
have other secrets?

16:53.099 --> 16:54.883
♪

16:54.926 --> 16:57.755
- Sometimes he'd tutor me.

16:57.799 --> 17:02.847
Sometimes
he'd massage my body.

17:02.891 --> 17:06.677
After dance, that felt
really good, but then he--

17:06.721 --> 17:09.289
♪

17:09.332 --> 17:11.378
I sh--I shouldn't talk
about this anymore.

17:11.421 --> 17:12.727
- Hey, Renee, listen to me.

17:12.770 --> 17:14.294
There's nothing
that you can tell us

17:14.337 --> 17:15.469
that we haven't heard before.

17:15.512 --> 17:17.210
♪

17:17.253 --> 17:19.690
- Can I just show you?

17:19.734 --> 17:26.871
♪

17:39.928 --> 17:43.105
I told Rev I had deleted it.

17:43.149 --> 17:45.151
That's why he gave me
the money.

17:45.194 --> 17:46.674
- How old were you here?

17:46.717 --> 17:48.850
- Fifteen.

17:48.893 --> 17:51.113
- Who is the man in this video?

17:51.157 --> 17:54.029
- Reverend Chase.

17:54.073 --> 18:00.992
♪

18:02.385 --> 18:04.170
[sniffles]

18:08.348 --> 18:08.522
.

18:08.565 --> 18:11.046
- Garland's a cop,
a deacon at the church.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.482
And he's telling us
he didn't know his own pastor

18:12.526 --> 18:14.484
was a child rapist?
- Fin.

18:14.528 --> 18:16.573
- I'm not saying he knew
and kept it quiet.

18:16.617 --> 18:19.837
I'm saying
he should've known something.

18:19.881 --> 18:22.144
Are we arresting
this guy or not?

18:22.188 --> 18:24.364
[doorbell rings]

18:26.061 --> 18:27.497
- Detectives.

18:27.541 --> 18:29.020
- Reverend Chase,
we'd like you to come with us

18:29.064 --> 18:30.326
down to the station.

18:30.370 --> 18:31.762
- Is this about
the embezzlement?

18:31.806 --> 18:34.635
- No, it's about Renee Lee.
- I don't understand.

18:34.678 --> 18:38.160
- She's made
an allegation of rape.

18:38.204 --> 18:39.901
- What did you say
to that poor girl?

18:39.944 --> 18:42.599
- She also has a tape.

18:42.643 --> 18:44.210
- Am I under arrest?

18:44.253 --> 18:45.863
- Not if you come with us
down to the station.

18:45.907 --> 18:47.691
We'd rather not cuff you.

18:47.735 --> 18:50.999
- Delman, what's wrong?
- Call Adams.

18:51.042 --> 18:53.044
And Christian Garland.

18:53.088 --> 18:55.873
- You should know that
Garland sent us.

18:55.917 --> 18:58.920
[tense music]

18:58.963 --> 19:01.183
- It's all right, baby.

19:01.227 --> 19:07.058
♪

19:07.102 --> 19:08.016
[knocking on door]

19:08.059 --> 19:10.453
[door opens]

19:10.497 --> 19:12.151
You knew he was
being brought in?

19:12.194 --> 19:13.239
- I did.

19:13.282 --> 19:14.544
- How could you
let this happen?

19:14.588 --> 19:16.242
After 15 years?

19:16.285 --> 19:18.113
We've eaten at
each other's table,

19:18.157 --> 19:20.376
prayed together.
He's Abby's godfather.

19:20.420 --> 19:24.511
- Laura, please sit down.
- Why is this girl lying, huh?

19:24.554 --> 19:26.948
Why does she want to hurt us?

19:26.991 --> 19:28.341
♪

19:28.384 --> 19:31.561
- There's a video.

19:31.605 --> 19:34.608
- I don't believe it.
I wanna see it.

19:34.651 --> 19:36.262
- I don't think--
- This is my husband's life

19:36.305 --> 19:38.264
we're talking about, Christian.
I wanna see it.

19:38.307 --> 19:45.445
♪

19:50.101 --> 19:52.191
[sighs sharply]

19:54.758 --> 19:58.719
[breathes nervously]
Thank God it's not him.

20:01.461 --> 20:02.810
So why are you
doing this, Christian?

20:02.853 --> 20:04.899
- Laura--
- It's a fake.

20:07.641 --> 20:11.558
That's not Del.
You need to tell them.

20:14.038 --> 20:15.301
Tell them.

20:15.344 --> 20:17.607
- What reason would
this girl have to lie?

20:17.651 --> 20:21.089
And the payments to her
and her family--

20:21.132 --> 20:24.701
$250,000?

20:24.745 --> 20:26.877
♪

20:26.921 --> 20:29.315
I can't make this go away!

20:29.358 --> 20:33.928
- If you can't...

20:33.971 --> 20:35.495
then our relationship is over.

20:35.538 --> 20:39.063
No one in our church will
ever speak to you

20:39.107 --> 20:41.892
or your wife

20:41.936 --> 20:44.286
or your little daughter again.

20:44.330 --> 20:51.424
♪

20:56.167 --> 20:58.257
[door slams]

20:58.300 --> 20:59.301
- Did he say anything
in the car?

20:59.345 --> 21:02.565
- He was very polite.
He prayed.

21:02.609 --> 21:05.525
- Olivia.

21:05.568 --> 21:06.830
- Edgar.

21:06.874 --> 21:09.572
- I'm here to see my client,
Reverend Chase.

21:09.616 --> 21:12.836
- You're a criminal attorney?
- Yeah, I used to be.

21:12.880 --> 21:14.229
But it doesn't matter.
Since Reverend Chase is not

21:14.273 --> 21:16.187
a criminal, he called me.

21:16.231 --> 21:17.450
I'm of counsel to the church.

21:17.493 --> 21:20.888
- I'm sorry to tell you this,

21:20.931 --> 21:22.803
but there--there may be

21:22.846 --> 21:25.893
a side to your client
that you're not aware of.

21:27.982 --> 21:31.072
- Where's Delman?

21:31.115 --> 21:32.682
Renee Lee
secretly recorded this?

21:32.726 --> 21:36.033
- Yes, and that's
clearly her in the tape.

21:36.077 --> 21:37.948
She was 15 years old.

21:37.992 --> 21:39.559
- That's the entirety
of the video?

21:39.602 --> 21:40.951
- What, you wanna see more?

21:40.995 --> 21:42.997
- Well, I see nothing
that implicates my client.

21:43.040 --> 21:44.825
All that's visible
is a black male torso.

21:44.868 --> 21:45.869
That could be anyone.

21:45.913 --> 21:47.349
- Renee said
that Reverend Chase

21:47.393 --> 21:50.352
sexually abused her
for three years,

21:50.396 --> 21:52.572
until six months ago.

21:52.615 --> 21:55.226
- Uh, my heart goes out
to the poor girl,

21:55.270 --> 21:58.360
but she's lying.
I need to talk to her.

21:58.404 --> 22:00.710
Pray with her.
- Shut her up?

22:00.754 --> 22:02.886
Wasn't that what
the $1/4 million was for?

22:02.930 --> 22:04.235
- That money,
given out of compassion,

22:04.279 --> 22:06.281
apparently only showed her
how deep my client's

22:06.325 --> 22:07.543
and the church's pockets are.

22:07.587 --> 22:09.371
This is obviously
an extortion attempt.

22:09.415 --> 22:11.460
- Renee didn't come to us.

22:11.504 --> 22:14.420
And at first, she said
that it was charity.

22:14.463 --> 22:16.857
- I-I think
she's troubled, confused.

22:16.900 --> 22:18.293
- Reverend--

22:18.337 --> 22:19.903
- These young girls
and their teenage temptations.

22:19.947 --> 22:22.558
- You sure know a lot about
their temptations, don't you?

22:22.602 --> 22:25.996
- She had
an unhealthy fixation on me.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.607
I prayed with her,

22:27.650 --> 22:29.739
told her it would pass.

22:29.783 --> 22:31.959
She must have found someone
else to act it out with.

22:32.002 --> 22:34.048
- Why would she say
that's you on the video?

22:34.091 --> 22:37.573
- Captain, Sergeant, we've
cooperated as much as we can.

22:37.617 --> 22:38.705
You have a girl here
with a history

22:38.748 --> 22:40.402
of drug and promiscuity issues

22:40.446 --> 22:42.883
against the word
of a renowned spiritual leader.

22:42.926 --> 22:44.450
I can't imagine this
goes any further.

22:44.493 --> 22:47.627
- Oh, it can.

22:49.150 --> 22:51.326
And it will.

22:52.936 --> 22:54.808
- Well, if your minds
are that closed,

22:54.851 --> 22:57.071
I'd like a few moments
alone with my attorney.

22:58.986 --> 23:02.119
"Blessed is the man who
remains steadfast under trial,

23:02.163 --> 23:04.295
"for when he has stood
the test he will receive

23:04.339 --> 23:05.558
the crown of life."

23:05.601 --> 23:06.907
- Yeah, now he's praying?
Little late.

23:06.950 --> 23:09.388
- Okay, while he prays,
can we get a subpoena

23:09.431 --> 23:10.737
to photograph his torso
and his back?

23:10.780 --> 23:12.608
- That's tough
unless we arrest.

23:12.652 --> 23:13.696
- He's not under arrest yet?

23:13.740 --> 23:15.132
- Garland's looking
out for him?

23:15.176 --> 23:16.438
- More like the Eighth Floor.

23:16.482 --> 23:17.613
And considering
the Reverend's profile--

23:17.657 --> 23:19.789
- And the voting bloc
he controls--

23:19.833 --> 23:22.923
- To be fair, Renee will be
a problematic witness.

23:22.966 --> 23:24.881
It would be helpful
if we had some corroboration.

23:24.925 --> 23:27.275
- Kat, comb through
the financials again

23:27.318 --> 23:28.450
and follow up with
any of the girls

23:28.494 --> 23:29.843
that we haven't contacted yet.

23:29.886 --> 23:32.149
- Copy that.
- Fin, Rollins.

23:32.193 --> 23:35.239
see if any of the girls
in the dorm might break rank.

23:35.283 --> 23:36.893
And then--
I know it's a long shot,

23:36.937 --> 23:39.853
but get CSU to go
through Renee's dorm.

23:44.727 --> 23:46.512
- When I went to Renee's room
to call her for lunch,

23:46.555 --> 23:48.557
she was gone.
She took everything.

23:48.601 --> 23:49.645
She must've run away.

23:49.689 --> 23:50.994
- What did you say
to her, Michelle?

23:51.038 --> 23:52.431
- Just that
she would have to swear

23:52.474 --> 23:53.823
on the Bible
to tell the truth.

23:53.867 --> 23:56.043
That lying lips are
an abomination to the Lord.

23:56.086 --> 23:57.436
- You know where she went?

23:57.479 --> 23:59.176
- Not a person in this church
would take her in.

23:59.220 --> 24:01.135
I heard her on the phone,
crying to her mother.

24:01.178 --> 24:02.441
- [crying]

24:02.484 --> 24:04.573
- Breyona, honey,
you can't be in here.

24:04.617 --> 24:06.270
- I know she brought this
on herself,

24:06.314 --> 24:08.490
but they didn't
have to do this.

24:10.710 --> 24:13.408
- Breyona's just a kid.
She don't know better.

24:13.452 --> 24:15.541
But no one else feels bad.

24:15.584 --> 24:16.977
Renee was lying
about the Reverend.

24:17.020 --> 24:19.501
She knew that if
she continued on that path,

24:19.545 --> 24:22.243
she'd be damning her soul
to hell for all eternity.

24:22.286 --> 24:25.246
[dramatic music]

24:25.289 --> 24:32.427
♪

24:37.954 --> 24:38.172
.

24:38.215 --> 24:40.000
- The Reverend was
having sex with Renee?

24:40.043 --> 24:40.957
[scoffs]
I don't believe it.

24:41.001 --> 24:43.133
R-Renee never said a word.

24:43.177 --> 24:45.005
And--and I would know.
I'm her mother.

24:45.048 --> 24:46.920
- Sometimes mothers
are the last to know.

24:46.963 --> 24:48.356
- [scoffs]

24:48.399 --> 24:51.011
He's a man of God.
He saved us from being a--

24:51.054 --> 24:52.708
- You mean with the money?

24:52.752 --> 24:54.928
He didn't make those payments
until he found out

24:54.971 --> 24:57.974
that Renee had a video
of them having sex.

25:00.063 --> 25:01.848
- Now you--you listen here.

25:01.891 --> 25:03.806
I've--I've paid my mortgage.

25:03.850 --> 25:06.722
So if you're looking for
that money back, it's gone.

25:06.766 --> 25:08.028
- That's not why we're here.

25:08.071 --> 25:09.377
- When's the last time
you heard from Renee?

25:09.420 --> 25:11.553
- She called me.

25:11.597 --> 25:13.163
Said the girls at the school
were being mean,

25:13.207 --> 25:14.556
and she couldn't
take it anymore.

25:14.600 --> 25:17.298
I told her life was
overcoming obstacles,

25:17.341 --> 25:18.908
and she couldn't come home
crying to Mommy

25:18.952 --> 25:20.606
just 'cause she had a bad day.

25:20.649 --> 25:22.999
- So she wanted to come home?
- Yes.

25:23.043 --> 25:25.785
- Any other place
she could've gone?

25:25.828 --> 25:27.264
- Just one.

25:30.093 --> 25:31.660
[knocking on door]

25:33.096 --> 25:34.141
- How'd you find me?

25:34.184 --> 25:35.838
- Your mom's worried about you.

25:35.882 --> 25:37.013
- You mean she's worried
about the money.

25:37.057 --> 25:38.362
- That too.

25:38.406 --> 25:40.539
Is your boyfriend home?
- He's at work.

25:40.582 --> 25:42.018
Anyway, the cops can't care
about that anymore.

25:42.062 --> 25:43.193
I'm 17.

25:43.237 --> 25:46.632
- We just wanna talk to you.

25:46.675 --> 25:48.547
- You can't convince me
to come back.

25:48.590 --> 25:51.332
Everyone's saying
I'm a gold digger, I'm a ho,

25:51.375 --> 25:53.595
just bringing a good man down.

25:53.639 --> 25:55.118
- We know that
he's not a good man.

25:55.162 --> 25:56.729
- You're cops.

25:56.772 --> 25:59.383
Everybody at church,
even if they see the video,

25:59.427 --> 26:00.776
they'll just say it's not him.

26:00.820 --> 26:02.735
- We show the video in court,
and you say it's him,

26:02.778 --> 26:04.084
a jury will know.

26:04.127 --> 26:06.129
- Why would I want that
shown in court?

26:06.173 --> 26:08.262
All those people--

26:08.305 --> 26:10.307
I never should've
shown it to you.

26:10.351 --> 26:14.007
If I kept my mouth shut
and kept the money,

26:14.050 --> 26:16.009
let him move on to
his next special girl--

26:16.052 --> 26:18.185
- Which girl?

26:18.228 --> 26:20.448
[dramatic music]

26:20.491 --> 26:23.669
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

26:23.712 --> 26:26.759
And you better get out of here
before Carl comes home.

26:26.802 --> 26:29.152
He hates cops.

26:29.196 --> 26:32.286
♪

26:32.329 --> 26:35.332
- Two decaf, one regular.
- Great.

26:35.376 --> 26:36.377
- Let me know if you
need anything else.

26:36.420 --> 26:38.988
- Thank you so much, Lamai.

26:41.861 --> 26:44.254
- Where were we?

26:44.298 --> 26:46.126
Uh, yeah, I was about to say

26:46.169 --> 26:47.780
we can make the case
without Renee.

26:47.823 --> 26:50.347
- That's what I would've
said too, when I was a cop.

26:50.391 --> 26:52.654
But her statement--
without the defense getting

26:52.698 --> 26:54.656
a chance to cross-examine her,
it won't be admissible.

26:54.700 --> 26:56.919
- What about the video?
- We can use it, but again,

26:56.963 --> 26:58.921
without Renee, we can't
even confirm that that's him

26:58.965 --> 27:00.531
on the tape.
- Okay, there is one way.

27:00.575 --> 27:04.100
If we arrest him, then
we can do a full body kit,

27:04.144 --> 27:06.146
get his DNA,
and photograph his torso.

27:06.189 --> 27:08.235
- It's the Captain's call,
not mine,

27:08.278 --> 27:10.716
but I do know the longer
we draw this out,

27:10.759 --> 27:12.674
the more time he'll have
to call in favors.

27:12.718 --> 27:17.113
- I'll give you a head start,
before I alert Ms. Hadid.

27:17.157 --> 27:19.681
- At the risk of overstepping,
can I ask that we

27:19.725 --> 27:21.988
not embarrass his wife
or the congregation

27:22.031 --> 27:24.599
by arresting him in public?

27:24.643 --> 27:26.949
- I will call his attorney
and--

27:26.993 --> 27:29.212
and arrange for the Reverend
to turn himself in.

27:29.256 --> 27:31.998
[foreboding music]

27:32.041 --> 27:35.175
[indistinct clamoring]

27:37.046 --> 27:38.308
- Hold on.

27:38.352 --> 27:41.181
Hey, Chief, doing okay?
- No.

27:41.224 --> 27:43.749
It's never easy
when mentors fall.

27:45.794 --> 27:48.710
Laura, can we talk?

27:51.408 --> 27:52.366
- You didn't have the decency

27:52.409 --> 27:53.497
to call him in yourself,
Christian?

27:53.541 --> 27:54.673
- I'm sorry.

27:54.716 --> 27:56.675
- [sighs]
I am too.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.546
He's not capable of this,
Christian.

27:58.589 --> 27:59.982
- I always--
- He's a good man.

28:00.026 --> 28:02.289
- I always thought so.

28:02.332 --> 28:05.205
That's why I refused
to believe it at first.

28:05.248 --> 28:07.860
- This girl Renee,
she must be out for our money.

28:07.903 --> 28:09.557
- It's not about money.

28:09.600 --> 28:12.560
She's been vilified by
her classmates, ostracized.

28:12.603 --> 28:14.040
This is the last thing
she wanted.

28:14.083 --> 28:17.217
- Maybe she's upset because
everybody knows she's lying.

28:17.260 --> 28:20.002
She's been to our home.
Delman looked out for her.

28:20.046 --> 28:22.352
He spent more time
tutoring her in math

28:22.396 --> 28:24.180
than he did working
on his own sermons.

28:24.224 --> 28:26.095
♪

28:26.139 --> 28:29.664
- And why is that, Laura?

28:29.708 --> 28:36.627
♪

28:42.242 --> 28:45.680
- Reverend Chase, on the charge
of rape in the second degree,

28:45.724 --> 28:48.248
how do you plead?
- Not guilty.

28:48.291 --> 28:50.337
- Not guilty, Your Honor.
- People on bail?

28:50.380 --> 28:51.904
- We request remand,
Your Honor.

28:51.947 --> 28:53.166
This charge is the first

28:53.209 --> 28:54.689
of what we believe
will be many others.

28:54.733 --> 28:57.170
He works with young women
in his church, at the school.

28:57.213 --> 28:58.867
We believe he's a risk.
- Your Honor,

28:58.911 --> 29:01.435
Reverend Chase has led a career
of profound public service,

29:01.478 --> 29:03.785
unblemished by
so much as a hint of scandal.

29:03.829 --> 29:06.179
He has no intention to flee,
only to clear his good name.

29:06.222 --> 29:08.268
We ask he be released
on his own recognizance.

29:08.311 --> 29:11.010
- I will grant bail
in the amount of 50,000,

29:11.053 --> 29:12.576
with the condition
the defendant

29:12.620 --> 29:14.622
has no unsupervised contact

29:14.665 --> 29:18.104
with any underage girls
pending trial.

29:18.147 --> 29:20.715
[indistinct chatter]

29:20.759 --> 29:23.457
[gavel raps]

29:23.500 --> 29:25.546
- I am grateful for
the prayers and support

29:25.589 --> 29:28.288
of my wife and co-pastor.
[cheers and applause]

29:28.331 --> 29:30.943
Even standing here
wrongfully accused,

29:30.986 --> 29:33.467
I'm a blessed man.

29:33.510 --> 29:35.948
- Turning courthouse steps
into his pulpit?

29:35.991 --> 29:37.210
You see that coming?

29:37.253 --> 29:39.516
- And his wife
standing by his side?

29:39.560 --> 29:41.388
- She perceives it
as her duty.

29:41.431 --> 29:42.781
Down to the dress
she's wearing.

29:42.824 --> 29:45.827
- There is no truth
to today's charges.

29:45.871 --> 29:48.395
My accuser is full of lies.
[crowd shouting in agreement]

29:48.438 --> 29:51.137
A girl who only seeks payment,

29:51.180 --> 29:52.703
who through perfidy
and deception,

29:52.747 --> 29:55.706
has stolen hard-earned dollars
from our church's coffers.

29:55.750 --> 29:58.840
But she's not alone
in her assault on our church.

29:58.884 --> 30:01.234
- Look, Chief, you don't need
to be here, really, let's--

30:01.277 --> 30:04.237
- If he's going to revile me,
I'd rather he do it to my face.

30:04.280 --> 30:05.847
- My calls to justice
have always been

30:05.891 --> 30:08.110
a threat to the NYPD,

30:08.154 --> 30:11.505
and they found a Judas
quick to do their bidding.

30:11.548 --> 30:13.899
And as Jesus forgave his Judas,

30:13.942 --> 30:15.857
I forgive my betrayer.

30:15.901 --> 30:17.903
[crowd cheers]

30:17.946 --> 30:20.340
Deputy Chief Garland,

30:20.383 --> 30:23.212
a member of my own flock,

30:23.256 --> 30:24.779
so eager to prove his worth

30:24.823 --> 30:27.608
to the lily-white establishment
of the NYPD,

30:27.651 --> 30:30.480
that he has concocted
a sickening conspiracy

30:30.524 --> 30:31.830
to try and bring me down.

30:31.873 --> 30:34.354
And I know there are those
who will believe

30:34.397 --> 30:36.617
and swallow these lies,

30:36.660 --> 30:38.575
like those who believed
the lies the Romans told

30:38.619 --> 30:41.927
about our Lord and Savior,
Jesus Christ.

30:41.970 --> 30:45.191
What did He do to deserve
being nailed on the cross?

30:45.234 --> 30:46.322
[crowd yells]

30:46.366 --> 30:48.977
- I can't.
- Yeah.

30:50.631 --> 30:52.851
- You okay, Chief?
- I've been cast out before.

30:52.894 --> 30:54.417
It's a recurring theme.
- [sighs]

30:54.461 --> 30:57.333
- Hey, listen,
don't take it personally.

30:57.377 --> 30:59.553
There's a reason
they call 'em a "flock."

30:59.596 --> 31:01.250
He'll never lose them.
- [sighs]

31:01.294 --> 31:03.687
Maybe.

31:03.731 --> 31:07.604
But I think he's losing the
one person he needs the most.

31:18.050 --> 31:18.224
.

31:18.267 --> 31:22.184
- Why don't you have
a seat right there?

31:22.228 --> 31:25.013
- Del has been lying to me
all these years.

31:25.057 --> 31:27.407
It's the first time
I've ever lied to him.

31:29.539 --> 31:32.412
He thinks I'm paying
a bereavement call.

31:33.108 --> 31:35.763
I didn't tell him that it was
you who called me last night.

31:35.806 --> 31:40.376
- Thank you for coming in.

31:40.420 --> 31:44.337
- After we spoke,
I thought about, uh...

31:44.380 --> 31:46.905
how--how did you say it?

31:46.948 --> 31:48.994
- I think that
I said that predators

31:49.037 --> 31:51.518
can often groom
their victims

31:51.561 --> 31:54.913
under the cover of mentoring.

31:54.956 --> 31:57.872
[soft dramatic music]

31:57.916 --> 32:02.529
- I was awake all night.

32:02.572 --> 32:06.620
All those hours Del
told me he was tutoring...

32:06.663 --> 32:10.580
♪

32:10.624 --> 32:13.888
My God, how could I let
that happen to those girls,

32:13.932 --> 32:16.325
under my watch?

32:16.369 --> 32:18.719
Under my roof?

32:18.762 --> 32:24.899
♪

32:24.943 --> 32:26.640
[sobs softly]

32:26.683 --> 32:29.991
This morning,

32:30.035 --> 32:32.124
I reached out to them.

32:32.167 --> 32:35.083
Michelle, Renee, Breyona.

32:35.127 --> 32:37.477
There could be others.
I have no idea.

32:37.520 --> 32:40.262
- And what did you say?

32:40.306 --> 32:44.440
- I asked for
their forgiveness.

32:44.484 --> 32:48.792
♪

32:48.836 --> 32:51.491
And I asked that
they cooperate with you.

33:04.983 --> 33:08.987
What did I do?
My God.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.955
- I couldn't believe
he knew my name.

33:20.999 --> 33:23.740
I felt so blessed.

33:23.784 --> 33:26.743
- And when did things change?

33:26.787 --> 33:31.009
- One night, he asked me
to stay late after practice.

33:31.052 --> 33:33.620
- That's when he offered
to give me a massage.

33:33.663 --> 33:35.491
- He was hugging me.

33:35.535 --> 33:37.798
It turned into a kiss.

33:37.841 --> 33:39.669
[tense music]

33:39.713 --> 33:42.063
He put his tongue
in my mouth.

33:42.107 --> 33:43.630
- He told me that

33:43.673 --> 33:46.894
he had never done this before
with any other girl.

33:46.937 --> 33:48.809
- That it would have
to be our secret.

33:48.852 --> 33:53.553
- That the feelings were
so strong, it was God's will.

33:53.596 --> 33:55.337
- Tell me about the video.

33:55.381 --> 33:57.035
♪

33:57.078 --> 33:59.863
- When he said he was
coming to my room again,

33:59.907 --> 34:02.997
I set up my laptop with
the video camera recording.

34:03.041 --> 34:05.695
- And when did you
show him the video?

34:05.739 --> 34:07.523
♪

34:07.567 --> 34:09.786
- Last November.

34:09.830 --> 34:13.616
I saw he was beginning
to pay attention to Breyona.

34:15.096 --> 34:16.793
I guess I was jealous.

34:16.837 --> 34:20.275
- I didn't understand at
the time why Renee was upset.

34:20.319 --> 34:22.799
- And did he offer you money?

34:22.843 --> 34:27.239
- He set up a scholarship fund
and gave me a job.

34:27.282 --> 34:30.546
- He bought my mom a car.

34:30.590 --> 34:33.723
- Four months ago,
after I showed him the video,

34:33.767 --> 34:37.118
he confiscated my computer,

34:37.162 --> 34:41.557
and he gave me
and my mother $250,000.

34:41.601 --> 34:45.300
- And was that Reverend Chase
in the video?

34:45.344 --> 34:47.520
- Yes.

34:47.563 --> 34:50.305
- And how old were you
at the time?

34:50.349 --> 34:53.134
- Fifteen.

34:53.178 --> 34:56.746
I know because I recorded it
on my birthday.

34:56.790 --> 35:02.143
♪

35:02.187 --> 35:05.277
- Thank you, Renee.

35:07.844 --> 35:09.933
Thank you for coming in.

35:09.977 --> 35:11.326
I wanted to give you
the heads-up

35:11.370 --> 35:14.155
that Renee Lee testified
before a grand jury today.

35:14.199 --> 35:16.244
It's pretty damning.

35:16.288 --> 35:18.420
- Renee.

35:18.464 --> 35:21.771
I see clearly now how
she led me to temptation.

35:21.815 --> 35:23.121
She's no innocent.

35:23.164 --> 35:24.339
She used her lithe body,

35:24.383 --> 35:26.515
her suggestive smile
to lure me to her,

35:26.559 --> 35:28.778
no different from Bathsheba,
bathing on the rooftop,

35:28.822 --> 35:30.128
20 yards from King David.

35:30.171 --> 35:31.651
- So you didn't assault her--

35:31.694 --> 35:33.305
- I would never assault anyone.
- More of a seduction?

35:33.348 --> 35:35.176
- You got that right.
Getting all gussied up

35:35.220 --> 35:37.091
every time I came over
to tutor her.

35:37.135 --> 35:39.137
She entrapped me.
Why else would she video--

35:39.180 --> 35:40.877
- Reverend--
- And--and then lie to me

35:40.921 --> 35:42.314
that she deleted the only copy?

35:42.357 --> 35:45.273
She's the one who should be
charged here with extortion.

35:45.317 --> 35:48.450
- Yeah, maybe.
But she was underage.

35:48.494 --> 35:52.193
- A jury will look at her,
and then at me,

35:52.237 --> 35:54.152
and decide for themselves.
- I hear you.

35:54.195 --> 35:57.459
And--and to be honest,
I-I'd be nervous,

35:57.503 --> 36:01.811
if I didn't have two other
girls from the church

36:01.855 --> 36:03.639
who also testified to

36:03.683 --> 36:06.425
the exact same pattern
of grooming, seduction,

36:06.468 --> 36:08.470
and sexual predation.
- Were these girls--

36:08.514 --> 36:11.952
- Underage?
All of them, at the start.

36:11.995 --> 36:14.563
By the time they turned 17,
the good Reverend here

36:14.607 --> 36:17.218
only seems to get tempted
by a younger girl.

36:17.262 --> 36:19.089
- T-they're setting me up.

36:19.133 --> 36:20.656
It's gotta be part
of a coordinated shakedown.

36:20.700 --> 36:23.050
They know the church has money.
Someone must've got to them.

36:23.093 --> 36:25.313
- Delman.
- Your client's right.

36:25.357 --> 36:26.967
Someone did meet with them.

36:27.010 --> 36:28.490
- To extort money
from the church?

36:28.534 --> 36:31.319
- No, to give them permission
to tell the truth,

36:31.363 --> 36:34.017
without fear of
reprisal from you.

36:34.061 --> 36:36.672
- I demand to know
who in my congregation

36:36.716 --> 36:37.847
would plot against me.

36:37.891 --> 36:40.328
- There's no plot, Reverend.

36:43.070 --> 36:44.506
She was seeking
their forgiveness.

36:44.550 --> 36:45.986
- "She"?

36:46.029 --> 36:47.683
- Your wife.

36:47.727 --> 36:49.555
♪

36:49.598 --> 36:51.861
- Laura?

36:51.905 --> 36:53.776
You--you turned her against me?

36:53.820 --> 36:55.865
- [scoffs]

36:55.909 --> 36:59.260
No, you did that.

36:59.304 --> 37:01.610
And she'll never
forgive herself

37:01.654 --> 37:04.091
for what happened
to those girls.

37:12.099 --> 37:14.232
[knocking on door]

37:14.275 --> 37:16.277
- Reverend Chase's
lawyer is here.

37:16.321 --> 37:17.670
Want me to tell him
to go away?

37:17.713 --> 37:21.717
- That's not a bad idea,
but, uh, no, thanks.

37:24.329 --> 37:26.766
- I'll be outside.
- Thanks, Fin.

37:28.376 --> 37:29.812
- Your sergeant's
protective of you.

37:29.856 --> 37:32.859
- Always.
So...

37:32.902 --> 37:34.077
the Reverend took the deal?

37:34.121 --> 37:35.296
- He did.

37:35.340 --> 37:36.819
I told him, going forward,
I can no longer

37:36.863 --> 37:39.561
be of counsel to the church
and represent him.

37:39.605 --> 37:43.261
So I arranged for
other counsel to take over.

37:45.263 --> 37:48.135
Can we talk off the record?

37:50.180 --> 37:52.139
- Of course.
Have a seat.

37:54.489 --> 37:56.491
- I want you to know
that I've gone over this

37:56.535 --> 37:58.493
in my head a hundred times.

37:58.537 --> 38:01.496
Never saw any of the signs.

38:01.540 --> 38:04.325
I'm sick over it and ashamed.

38:04.369 --> 38:08.155
- If it helps, I've heard
hundreds of spouses,

38:08.198 --> 38:11.332
of friends, of parents...

38:11.376 --> 38:14.161
tell me exactly
what you're telling me.

38:14.204 --> 38:15.554
When there's
a skilled predator,

38:15.597 --> 38:17.295
one that's been
operating for decades,

38:17.338 --> 38:21.821
they are adept at
shielding their dark side

38:21.864 --> 38:24.302
from everyone,

38:24.345 --> 38:26.434
except their victims.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.350
- A wolf in sheep's clothing.

38:29.394 --> 38:32.353
[somber music]

38:32.397 --> 38:34.834
And I am so sorry
for my part in this.

38:34.877 --> 38:36.923
♪

38:36.966 --> 38:40.405
- You were doing your job,
defending your client.

38:40.448 --> 38:42.711
- What he did,
there is no defense.

38:42.755 --> 38:49.239
♪

38:49.283 --> 38:52.678
- Counselor, um,
for what it's worth,

38:52.721 --> 38:57.596
I wish we hadn't met
under these circumstances.

38:59.337 --> 39:01.600
- [breathes deeply]

39:03.645 --> 39:06.387
Me too.

39:06.431 --> 39:09.869
♪

39:09.912 --> 39:12.480
[gate buzzes and opens]

39:13.829 --> 39:16.441
- Christian.
It was good of you to come.

39:16.484 --> 39:17.529
- How are you, Delman?

39:17.572 --> 39:18.921
- Enduring the tribulations

39:18.965 --> 39:22.403
the Lord has deemed
fit to send me.

39:22.447 --> 39:24.753
- I was relieved to hear
you decided to plead guilty.

39:24.797 --> 39:26.494
- I wanted to spare
the young women

39:26.538 --> 39:28.670
the burden of
having to testify.

39:28.714 --> 39:32.239
- You mean spare yourself
the humiliation?

39:33.066 --> 39:35.024
- You sound angry, Christian.

39:35.068 --> 39:36.722
- I'm struggling.

39:36.765 --> 39:39.464
- You wanna talk about that?
- Not with you.

39:39.507 --> 39:42.205
- Then why are you here?
To gloat?

39:42.249 --> 39:43.598
To castigate?

39:43.642 --> 39:46.427
Other than my new lawyer,
you're my only visitor.

39:46.471 --> 39:48.429
Laura won't even take
my phone calls.

39:48.473 --> 39:51.214
- Do you blame her?

39:51.258 --> 39:54.435
- You know, Laura and I were
never able to have a child?

39:54.479 --> 39:56.568
And I thought
God was testing me,

39:56.611 --> 39:58.831
and that was
the worst punishment

39:58.874 --> 40:00.789
He could visit on me.

40:00.833 --> 40:02.835
But now, to knock me down
like this,

40:02.878 --> 40:05.446
take away my church,
put me behind bars--

40:05.490 --> 40:08.101
- You're not Job in this story.
Laura is.

40:08.144 --> 40:11.713
- No, He's testing me.

40:11.757 --> 40:14.324
God hasn't abandoned me,
Christian.

40:14.368 --> 40:16.414
This is all a part of His plan.

40:16.457 --> 40:18.241
He wants me to minister
to the souls

40:18.285 --> 40:20.635
of all the men
behind these bars.

40:20.679 --> 40:24.160
That's why He did this to me.
- You did this to yourself.

40:24.204 --> 40:27.076
And until you realize that,
there's no path to forgiveness

40:27.120 --> 40:29.470
from Laura, me, or God.

40:29.514 --> 40:30.732
♪

40:30.776 --> 40:35.128
- Well, then.
You've said your piece.

40:35.171 --> 40:37.043
You needn't visit again.

40:37.086 --> 40:41.003
Tomas?

40:41.047 --> 40:42.657
[gate buzzes and opens]

40:42.701 --> 40:44.224
- Delman.

40:44.267 --> 40:45.617
[gate creaks]

40:48.054 --> 40:50.535
I will pray for you.

40:50.578 --> 40:53.755
[dramatic music]

40:53.799 --> 41:00.719
♪

41:16.909 --> 41:17.126
.

41:17.170 --> 41:20.129
[dramatic music]

41:20.173 --> 41:27.049
♪

41:46.373 --> 41:48.549
[wolf howls]
